'lastpass-vs-1password-2026': [
  { heading: 'LastPass vs 1Password 2026: Can LastPass Recover from the 2022 Breach?', paragraphs: [
    '<div class="bg-emerald-950 border border-emerald-800 rounded-xl p-4 mb-4 text-sm text-emerald-300"><strong>Affiliate Disclosure:</strong> Some links are affiliate links — at no extra cost to you. Our analysis is independent, including the breach discussion below.</div>',
    'LastPass suffered a major breach in August 2022. Attackers accessed encrypted password vaults. If your master password was weak, those vaults could be decrypted by attackers. If your master password was strong (16+ random characters), the vaults are practically uncrackable. The breach was serious — LastPass\'s handling of disclosure was widely criticized as evasive.',
  ]},
  { heading: 'Current State Comparison', paragraphs: [
    '<div class="overflow-x-auto my-4"><table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse"><thead><tr class="bg-gray-800"><th class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-left text-white">Factor</th><th class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-left text-red-400">LastPass</th><th class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-left text-blue-400">1Password</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="hover:bg-gray-800"><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">Major breach history</td><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">Yes (2022, critical)</td><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">No</td></tr><tr class="hover:bg-gray-800"><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">Breach transparency</td><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">Poor</td><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">N/A</td></tr><tr class="hover:bg-gray-800"><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">Current price (individual)</td><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">$3/mo</td><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">$2.99/mo</td></tr><tr class="hover:bg-gray-800"><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">Free tier</td><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">Limited (1 device type)</td><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">No</td></tr><tr class="hover:bg-gray-800"><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">Security architecture</td><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">Standard</td><td class="border border-gray-700 p-3 text-gray-300">Secret key + master pwd</td></tr></tbody></table></div>',
    '1Password uses a "secret key" — a 34-character key generated locally during setup. Your vault encryption requires both your master password AND this secret key. Even if servers are breached, attackers cannot decrypt vaults without this locally-generated key. LastPass\'s architecture does not include a comparable second secret, which is why the 2022 breach resulted in encrypted vaults being stolen (and potentially crackable).',
    'LastPass has improved security protocols post-breach: 600,000 PBKDF2 iterations (increased from 5,000), better monitoring, and forced master password resets for many users. But trust, once broken, is hard to restore.',
  ]},
  { heading: 'Verdict', paragraphs: [
    '1Password. The pricing is nearly identical and 1Password has never suffered a major breach. The secret key architecture is genuinely more secure. There\'s no compelling reason to choose LastPass when 1Password offers equivalent price and superior security track record. If cost is the constraint, use Bitwarden — it\'s free and open-source.',
  ]},
  { heading: 'Frequently Asked Questions', paragraphs: [
    'Q: Should I still use LastPass after the 2022 breach?\nA: If you had a strong master password (16+ random characters), your vault is likely still secure. We still recommend migrating to 1Password or Bitwarden — not because LastPass is currently unsafe, but because trust and architecture both favor alternatives.',
    'Q: Did anyone actually get hacked from the LastPass breach?\nA: Yes. In 2023, approximately $35 million in cryptocurrency was stolen from LastPass users — attackers decrypted weaker vaults. Users with strong master passwords appear unaffected.',
    'Q: How do I migrate from LastPass to 1Password?\nA: LastPass exports to CSV. 1Password imports LastPass CSV format directly. The migration wizard handles the transfer. The process takes 10-15 minutes.',
  ]},
],

